sentences: Sidney De Paris (May 30, 1905 – September 13, 1967) was an American jazz trumpeter.

He was a member of Charlie Johnson's Paradise Ten (1926–1931), worked with Don Redman (1932–1936 and 1939), followed by periods with Zutty Singleton (1939–1941), Benny Carter (1940–41), and Art Hodes (1941).
